# Rth Installation

Below, the installation directory is ~/R; change as desired.

## OpenMP

Assuming you have an OpenMP-compatible C++ compiler (on a Mac, install the OpenMP-compatible version of clang):

    R CMD INSTALL -l ~/R Rth_0.1-0.tar.gz \
      --configure-args="--with-backend=OPENMP"



## Intel Thread Building Blocks


    R CMD INSTALL -l ~/R Rth_0.1-0.tar.gz \
      --configure-args="--with-backend=TBB \
      --with-tbb-incdir=$TBBINC --with-tbb-libdir=$TBBLIB"



## CUDA

    R CMD INSTALL -l ~/R Rth_0.1-0.tar.gz \
      --configure-args="--with-backend=CUDA"
